comments.body:
@daniel-luberda I have merged your changes into the development branch - this is where I think we should work from in the future so that master is always in a "releasable" state.

I made a few changes because I wanted to "capitalize" (sounds like a nice word here) on you splitting the gradient logic out into a separate type instead of inline processing.

I did notice that as a result of supporting more advanced gradients. You should be able to run the tests in the Visual Studio IDE. I am going to do a bit more testing to see if I broke something, or maybe it was your changes or what actually happened.
